In Kubernetes, we can pass environment variables to containers in a Pod using the env field. 
- Static values
- Values from ConfigMaps or Secrets



```
    kubectl apply -f secrets.yaml
    kubectl apply -f pod.yaml

    echo -n "admin" | base64
    YWRtaW4=

    echo -n "Admin123" | base64
    QWRtaW4xMjM=

    echo -n "QWRtaW4xMjM=" | base64  --decode
    Admin123

    echo -n "YWRtaW4=" | base64  --decode
    admin




```